Risk Predction_Analysis

Chathurika Hettiarachchige

November 11, 2018

This document consist of the code required to reproduce the analysis presented in the paper titled Risk prediction system for dengue transmission based on high resolution weather data.

We split the data set chronologically, such that approximately 75% of the data is assigned to the training set and the remaining to the test set. We choose the date to split the data such that it is a start of a week, which is also the closest to the date that splits the full data set as above.

The data collected before 2012-09-23 is considered as training set and the rest as test set.

Stage 1: Predicting the Mosquito Presence

We performed a multivariate logistic regression to fit a model for the presence/absence 196 of larvae. Following is the multivariate logistic regression, and the treshold which maximises the sum of sensitivity and specificity. (Results for Table 1 on the paper.)

## 
## Call:
## glm(formula = larvaB ~ MaxTemp + MaxPrecip + AvgRHumi + AvgHGT + 
##     MaxTemp:AvgRHumi + MaxTemp:AvgHGT + MaxPrecip:AvgHGT + MaxPrecip:AvgRHumi + 
##     MaxTemp:MaxPrecip + offset(Con), family = binomial(link = "logit"), 
##     data = df2)

Stage 2: Estimating the Mosquito Numbers

Here we fit a zero-inflated negative binomial model to estimate the mosquito numbers for the counties determined as positive in the Stage 1.

## 
## Call:
## zeroinfl(formula = larva ~ MaxTemp + MaxPrecip + AvgRHumi + AvgHGT + 
##     offset(Con), data = df, dist = "negbin", EM = TRUE)
